## Tips for Effective Prompts

### Do
- Be specific about expected output
- Include relevant file paths
- Set realistic priorities
- Provide enough context

### Don't
- Write vague instructions ("make it better")
- Skip the context section
- Mark everything P0
- Duplicate prompts across sessions

---

## Integration

### Slash Command
Use `/start-task` to have Claude check this file automatically.

### Session Start
Claude should check this file when you begin a session with no specific task.

### Linking Outputs
Always link completed prompt outputs:
```markdown
> [!DONE] 2025-12-14
> **Output:** [[path/to/created/document.md]]
```

